HEADWORD: Pappus
<hw>Pap"pus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., an old man or
grandfather; hence, a substance resembling gray hairs, Gr. <?/.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The hairy or feathery appendage of the achenes of
thistles, dandelions, and most other plants of the order
<ord>Composit⟦ae⟧</ord>; also, the scales, awns, or bristles which
represent the calyx in other plants of the same order.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pappy</ent>⟦br⟧
